  "local_port": 48668,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I shake off these cruel feelings of want, so that I can maintain a healthy friendship before he inevitably loses interest and ditches me?",
  "response": "It's tough to navigate feelings of want, especially when they're complicated by the fear of losing someone. Here are some strategies to help you maintain a healthy friendship while managing those feelings:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**: Accept that it's normal to have strong feelings for someone you care about. Recognizing and accepting your emotions can help you feel more in control.\n\n2. **Set Boundaries**: Define what you need for your own emotional well-being. This might mean spending less time together or engaging in group activities rather than one-on-one interactions.\n\n3. **Focus on Friendship**: Remind yourself of the qualities that make the friendship special. Engage in activities that strengthen your bond without the pressure of romantic expectations.\n\n4. **Redirect Your Energy**: Invest your time and energy into hobbies, interests, or friendships that fulfill you. This can help divert your focus away from your feelings for this person.\n\n5. **Communicate Openly**: If appropriate, consider discussing your feelings with him. This doesn\u2019t have to lead to a romantic conversation but may help clarify where you both stand.\n\n6. **Limit Comparisons**: Avoid comparing your relationship with him to what you perceive in romantic relationships. Each friendship is unique and valuable in its own way.\n\n7. **Practice Mindfulness**: Use mindfulness techniques like meditation or journaling to help ground yourself in the present moment, which can provide relief from overwhelming feelings.\n\n8. **Seek Support**: Talk to friends or a professional about what you're going through. Having an outside perspective can be very helpful.\n\n9. **Stay Open to Possibilities**: Keep your heart open. Whether the friendship evolves or not, there are plenty of opportunities for connection and love in the future.\n\n10. **Self-Reflection**: Take the time to understand what you truly want and need in your relationships. This can provide clarity and help you make healthier choices going forward.\n\nRemember, friendships can be deep and meaningful even without romantic involvement, and it\u2019s possible to find fulfillment in that type of relationship. Focus on the positive aspects of your connection and give it the space to grow in whatever direction it's meant to go.",
